section.def:
compounded food (合成食物) means food containing 2 or more ingredients other than functional
            ingredients;
                    (L.N. 106 of 2015)

subparagraph.content:
constitutes one of the ingredients of any compounded food;
                                (L.N. 106 of
                            2015)

paragraph.content:
to serve any other technological function in relation to the food;
                            (L.N. 106 of
                        2015)

subparagraph.content:
that all necessary precautions for the prevention of danger to public
                        health were taken in the dressing or preparing and packing of the meat;
                        and

did not suffer any spoilage or deterioration during their stay there;
                                (L.N. 106 of
                            2015)

without having obtained a permission in writing of a health officer
                        that the officer may give for the purposes of this subregulation;
                        or
